         <abstract>
            <p>A Poisson equation on a rectangular domain is solved by coupling two methods: the domain is divided in two squares; a finite element approximation is used on the first square and a spectral discretization is used on the second. Two kinds of matching conditions on the interface are presented and compared; in both cases, error estimates are proved.</p>
          </abstract>
